  "prompt": "Is there any Part time universities in Hamburg where we can pursue MS?",
  "response": "In Hamburg, Germany, there are a few options for pursuing a Master's degree on a part-time basis. Here are some universities and programs you might consider:\n\n1. **Hamburg University of Technology (TUHH)**\n   - TUHH offers part-time Master's programs, particularly in engineering and technology-related fields. You can check their website for specific part-time offerings.\n\n2. **Hamburg University (Universit\u00e4t Hamburg)**\n   - Universit\u00e4t Hamburg has a variety of Master's programs, and some of them might be available on a part-time basis. It's best to contact their admissions office directly to inquire about part-time options.\n\n3. **Helmut Schmidt University**\n   - This university offers part-time programs, especially tailored for working professionals. Check their website for available Master's programs.\n\n4. **Hamburg University of Applied Sciences (HAW Hamburg)**\n   - HAW Hamburg provides some part-time Master's programs, often designed for professionals looking to advance their careers. Look into their offerings for more details.\n\n5. **Akademie der K\u00fcnste (AdK)**\n   - If you're interested in arts, AdK might offer part-time programs in certain fields. It's worth checking their specific offerings.\n\nWhen looking into these programs, consider the following steps:\n- **Check Program Availability**: Ensure that the Master's program you're interested in is offered on a part-time basis.\n- **Admission Requirements**: Verify the admission criteria, as they might differ for part-time students.\n- **Course Schedule**: Part-time programs often have different schedules, so make sure they fit with your other commitments.\n- **Contact Admissions**: It's always a good idea to reach out to the admissions office for the most current and specific information.\n\nRemember that availability and details can change, so it's important to stay updated through the universities' official websites and direct communication.",
